        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 5:42PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 541 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Skyline, or 10 miles northwest of Scottsboro, moving southwest at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gurley, Woodville, Pleasant Groves, Paint Rock, Lim Rock, Trenton,
Garth, and Hollytree.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
